3.  Soil specialist (carbon) (international, 4 person-months). The specialist will have the 
main  responsibility  for  the  management  of  output  2,  including  conduct  of  field  studies  to 
establish the carbon baselines, sequestration potentials, and monitoring methodologies. The 
specialist will have at least 10 years of international professional experience, preferably also in 
the PRC and Mongolia. The specialist will 

(i)  establish baselines at the demonstration sites regarding the rate of lost soil 
carbon saturation;  
(ii)  identify the link between conditions of grasslands and occurrence of dust and 
sandstorms; 
(iii)  prepare quantitative estimates of carbon sinks, according to representative types 
and states of degraded grasslands;  
(iv)  design a soil carbon monitoring network for the demonstration sites; 
(v)  define the methodologies for the establishment of baselines; and measurement 
and/or monitoring, reporting, and verification of carbon dioxide sequestered;  
(vi)  develop methodological guidelines for the assessment and monitoring of soil 
carbon, including a practical approach to extrapolating field measurement data 
(output 3, to be published as ADB knowledge product by month 18); 
(vii)  compile  and  prepare  the  final  report  on  carbon  sequestration  potential  and 
monitoring of grasslands in Northeast Asia (to be published as ADB knowledge 
product by month 22); 
(viii)  provide training to government counterpart staff; and 
(ix)  participate in regional workshops and conferences.  

4.  Social  development  specialist  (international,  4  person-months).  The  specialist  will 
have the overall responsibility to manage output 3, including raising the awareness of and 
liaising with the local stakeholders at the demonstration sites. The specialist will have at least 10 
years of international professional experience, preferably also in the PRC and Mongolia. The 
specialist will 

(i)  assess opportunities for and barriers to community participation in accessing 
carbon markets; 
(ii)  review international experiences with payment for environmental services and 
land tenure practices, including in Northeast Asia; 
(iii)  review current policy and regulatory frameworks for grassland management;  
(iv)  consult the key stakeholders at the eight demonstration sites; 
(v)  assess institutional arrangements to maximize ownership of the beneficiaries; 
(vi)  draft methodologies for preparing community agreements for accessing carbon 
financing through voluntary carbon markets; 
(vii)  prepare training materials to raise awareness of the grassland sequestration 
potential;

