(v)  in cooperation with the social development specialist, assess opportunities for 
and barriers to community participation in accessing carbon markets; 
(vi)  consult the key stakeholders at the four national demonstration sites; 
(vii)  assess institutional arrangements to maximize ownership by the beneficiaries of 
the potential projects; 
(viii)  prepare a national report on grassland management practices and opportunities 
for more sustainable management practices; 
(ix)  provide training to government counterpart staff; and 
(x)  participate in regional workshops and conferences.  

7.  Social development specialist (national, 2 consultants, 8 person-months each). The 
specialist will work closely with the international grassland management and social development 
specialist. The specialist will have a good command of the English language and have at least 8 
years of professional experience, preferably also in international donor-funded projects. The 
specialist will  

(i)  help  evaluate  opportunities  for  and  barriers  to  community  participation  in 
accessing carbon markets; 
(ii)  provide  inputs  to  the  review  of  international  experiences  with  payment  for 
environmental services and tenure practices in Northeast Asia; 
(iii)  in  cooperation  with  the  grassland  management  specialist,  consult  the  key 
stakeholders at the four national demonstration sites; 
(iv)  assess institutional arrangements to maximize ownership by the beneficiaries of 
the potential projects; 
(v)  help establish methodologies for preparing community agreements for accessing 
carbon financing through voluntary carbon markets; 
(vi)  contribute  to  the  preparation  of  training  materials  to  raise  awareness  of  the 
grassland sequestration potential; 
(vii)  help organize a regional workshop on community participation in developing 
carbon financing opportunities for more sustainable grassland management in 
Northeast Asia; 
(viii)  prepare a national report on approaches to community participation in voluntary 
carbon markets through better grassland management in Northeast Asia; 
(ix)  provide training to government counterpart staff; and 
(x)  participate in regional workshops and conferences.  

8.  Communication and translation officer (national, 2 consultants, 16 person-months 
each).  The  officer  will  support  the  climate  change  specialist  and  national  coordinator  in 
facilitating information sharing within the national team and ensuring the quality of the national 
reports and project outputs. The officer will have a good command of the English language and 
have at least 5 years of experience, preferably also in international donor-funded projects. The 
officer will 

(i)  support the liaison between the international consultant team, the government 
implementing agency, the national technical working group, and ADB; 
(ii)  provide administrative support for the national technical working group; 
(iii)  develop, maintain, and contribute to the project's website; 
(iv)  support the grassland management specialist and social development specialist 
in  preparing  materials  to  raise  awareness  of  the  grassland  sequestration 
potential; 
